str:Concept.com:Name: Frequency
str:Concept.com:Description: Indicates rate of recurrence at which observations occur (e.g. monthly, yearly, biannually, etc.).

str:Concept.com:Name: Reference Area
str:Concept.com:Description: Reference Area: Specific areas (e.g. Country, Regional Grouping, etc) the observed values refer to. Reference areas can be determined according to different criteria (e.g.: geographical, economic, etc.).

str:Concept.com:Name: Series
str:Concept.com:Description: The phenomenon or phenomena to be measured in the data set. The word SERIES is used for consistency with the term used in the WDI Database. SERIES are 54 key indicators from WDI

str:Concept.com:Name: Time period
str:Concept.com:Description: Reference date - or date range - the observed value refers to (usually different from the dates of data production or dissemination).

str:Concept.com:Name: Unit multiplier
str:Concept.com:Description: Exponent in base 10 that multiplied by the observation numeric value gives the result expressed in the unit of measure.
